 {"id":"bd-mblr.5.2","title":"Wire Structured Logging into realdb-e2e","description":"Integrate logging initialization and lifecycle in realdb-e2e so run/bench/corrupt/compare flows emit consistent machine-readable logs with correlation metadata and explicit run identifiers.","design":"Adopt shared logging core from schema task and add command adapters only for truly command-unique fields.","acceptance_criteria":"- realdb-e2e commands share consistent structured logging bootstrap and context propagation.
- Logs from run/bench/corrupt/compare use unified event naming and required field set.
- Command-specific metadata is included without fragmenting schema compatibility.","notes":"Consistency across e2e-runner and realdb-e2e is required for unified report tooling.","status":"open","priority":1,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-02-12T23:24:25.818667833Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-02-13T00:05:48.836023668Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"bd-mblr.5.2","depends_on_id":"bd-mblr.5","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-02-12T23:24:25.818667833Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-mblr.5.2","depends_on_id":"bd-mblr.5.3","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-02-12T23:25:11.787968019Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}],"comments":[{"id":1347,"issue_id":"bd-mblr.5.2","author":"Dicklesworthstone","text":"Implementation note: include run_id/workload_id/fixture_id and reproducibility metadata in each emitted event stream so logs can be joined with output JSONL summaries.","created_at":"2026-02-12T23:26:13Z"}]}
 {"id":"bd-mblr.5.2.1","title":"Wire structured logging initialization in realdb-e2e","description":"Ensure realdb-e2e initializes structured logging consistently across run/bench/corrupt/compare commands. Output: unified initialization path with command metadata.","design":"Insert structured bootstrap at command dispatch boundary and propagate context via typed event payload helpers.","acceptance_criteria":"- realdb-e2e initialization path emits deterministic structured events for every command mode.
- Required correlation fields (run_id, command, scenario_id/fixture_id, seed) are present when applicable.
- Automated checks prevent regressions to ad-hoc plaintext-only logging.","notes":"Align field semantics with e2e-runner to keep cross-tool analytics and triage simple.","status":"open","priority":1,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-02-12T23:38:07.096998084Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-02-13T00:05:48.912117940Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"bd-mblr.5.2.1","depends_on_id":"bd-mblr.5.2","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-02-12T23:38:07.096998084Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-mblr.5.2.1","depends_on_id":"bd-mblr.5.3.1","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-02-12T23:38:36.637181571Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}]}
 {"id":"bd-mblr.5.3","title":"Unified E2E Log Event Schema","description":"Define and enforce a stable event schema across all e2e logs (run_id, test_id, stage, operation, seed, fixture, worker, duration_ms, outcome, error_code, artifact_paths). Ensure backward-compatible parser support in report tooling.","design":"Use strongly typed event contracts plus schema-version tagging to enforce consistency at compile/test time.","acceptance_criteria":"- Unified E2E event schema is versioned, documented, and enforced in emitters/parsers.
- Required fields and allowed optional extensions are explicit and validated.
- Compatibility policy for schema evolution is defined with migration guidance.","notes":"Schema drift is a primary source of triage pain; strict contract governance is mandatory.","status":"open","priority":1,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-02-12T23:24:29.299879393Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-02-13T00:05:48.984717178Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"bd-mblr.5.3","depends_on_id":"bd-mblr.4.1","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-02-12T23:25:11.269577580Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-mblr.5.3","depends_on_id":"bd-mblr.5","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-02-12T23:24:29.299879393Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}]}
-{"id":"bd-mblr.5.3.1","title":"Unified E2E event schema spec + versioning","description":"Define required event fields, schema versioning rules, and compatibility policy for E2E logs. Output: schema contract document and code constants.","design":"Represent schema in machine-readable form (or typed model) and generate docs/examples from that source.","acceptance_criteria":"- Schema spec defines required fields, types, semantics, and allowed value ranges.
- Versioning policy covers additive vs breaking changes and upgrade behavior for tooling.
- Contract tests validate canonical event examples against schema definitions.","notes":"Schema must include replayability keys (scenario_id, seed, phase, invariant_ids, artifact_paths). Detailed scenario/artifact linkage is finalized during migration/conformance tasks rather than blocking initial schema drafting.","status":"open","priority":1,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-02-12T23:38:07.352853263Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-02-13T00:43:36.672185267Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"bd-mblr.5.3.1","depends_on_id":"bd-mblr.5.3","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-02-12T23:38:07.352853263Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}]}
